{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858762636,"sessionID":"ses_28691e9f7ffeHyKWAQxYcoGoNu","part":{"id":"prt_d796e3fef001wsLBBANBvLgARy","messageID":"msg_d796e36d3001dz34XbFBS9oEkR","sessionID":"ses_28691e9f7ffeHyKWAQxYcoGoNu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_6740597e18a743dcbc32dab8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement a Kubernetes controller in `pkg/agentd` that automatically cleans up idle `Sandbox` resources by detecting the `last-activity-time` annotation and deleting sandboxes that have been inactive beyond a 15-minute threshold.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The agentcube platform creates `Sandbox` resources via the workload-manager to manage execution environments. These sandboxes consume cluster resources even when they're no longer actively processing requests. Currently, there is no mechanism to automatically clean up these idle resources, leading to resource accumulation over time.\n12: \n13: ### Goal\n14: \n15: Create a dedicated controller (`agentd`) that:\n16: - Watches `Sandbox` resources with the `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1` API group\n17: - Reads the `last-activity-time` annotation set by workload-manager\n18: - Deletes sandboxes that have been idle beyond the configured threshold\n19: \n20: ### Value\n21: \n22: - Automatic resource cleanup reduces cluster resource consumption\n23: - Eliminates manual intervention for stale sandbox removal\n24: - Improves system reliability by preventing resource exhaustion\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## Scope\n29: \n30: ### In-Scope\n31: \n32: | Deliverable | Description |\n33: |-------------|-------------|\n34: | pkg/agentd package | Core reconciliation logic for idle cleanup |\n35: | cmd/agentd/main.go | Binary entry point with controller-runtime manager |\n36: | Reconciler implementation | Watch and delete idle Sandbox resources |\n37: | Configuration | SessionExpirationTimeout constant (15 minutes) |\n38: \n39: ### Code Structure\n40: \n41: ```\n42: cmd/agentd/\n43: └── main.go                  # Binary entry point\n44: \n45: pkg/agentd/\n46: └── reconciler.go            # Idle cleanup controller\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Out-of-Scope\n50: \n51: - Multiple timeout configuration (fixed 15-minute threshold)\n52: - Graceful shutdown coordination with workload-manager\n53: - Metrics and observability for cleanup operations\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## Impact Analysis\n58: \n59: ### Dependencies\n60: \n61: | Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n62: |------------|--------|---------|\n63: | sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime | v0.19.x | Controller framework |\n64: | k8s.io/apimachinery | existing | Kubernetes types |\n65: | sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1 | existing | Sandbox CRD |\n66: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager | existing | Annotation key constant |\n67: \n68: ### Upstream\n69: \n70: - **AR-012 Workload Manager** — Sets `last-activity-time` annotation on Sandbox resources\n71: - **Sandbox CRD** — Defines the `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1` API group\n72: \n73: ### Downstream Consumers\n74: \n75: 1. **Kubernetes Cluster** — Reduced resource pressure from idle sandboxes\n76: 2. **System Operators** — Automated cleanup without manual intervention\n77: \n78: ### Risks\n79: \n80: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n81: |------|----------|------------|\n82: | Annotation missing causes no cleanup | Low | Controller ignores sandboxes without annotation; requires workload-manager to set it |\n83: | Race condition with workload-manager | Low | Workload-manager updates annotation on activity; 15-min threshold provides buffer |\n84: | Delete failure causes retry storm | Medium | Return error only for non-NotFound delete failures |\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## Alternatives Considered\n89: \n90: ### Option 1: TTL Controller (Baseline)\n91: \n92: **Approach**: Use Kubernetes TTL Controller mechanism with `ttl` field on Sandbox.\n93: \n94: **Pros**:\n95: - Native Kubernetes pattern\n96: - No custom controller needed\n97: - Well-understood behavior\n98: \n99: **Cons**:\n100: - Requires modifying Sandbox CRD schema\n101: - TTL is immutable after creation (can't extend on activity)\n102: - No fine-grained control over timeout duration\n103: \n104: **Decision**: Not selected — incompatible with activity-based extension model.\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ### Option 2: Annotation-Based Cleanup (Selected)\n109: \n110: **Approach**: Read `last-activity-time` annotation and delete after 15-minute threshold.\n111: \n112: **Pros**:\n113: - Leverages existing annotation from workload-manager\n114: - No CRD schema changes required\n115: - Activity updates extend the idle window naturally\n116: \n117: **Cons**:\n118: - Requires coordination with workload-manager\n119: - Fixed timeout (not configurable per-sandbox)\n120: \n121: **Decision**: Selected — aligns with existing architecture and workload-manager patterns.\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ### Option 3: Finalizer-Based Cleanup\n126: \n127: **Approach**: Add finalizer to Sandbox that triggers cleanup on deletion.\n128: \n129: **Pros**:\n130: - Guaranteed cleanup on Sandbox deletion\n131: - Can implement complex cleanup logic\n132: \n133: **Cons**:\n134: - Requires modifying all Sandbox create paths\n135: - Adds complexity to workload-manager\n136: - Over-engineered for simple idle cleanup\n137: \n138: **Decision**: Not selected — adds unnecessary complexity to workload-manager.\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## Implementation Plan\n143: \n144: ### Phase 1: Package Structure\n145: - [ ] Create pkg/agentd package\n146: - [ ] Define SessionExpirationTimeout constant\n147: - [ ] Import workloadmanager for annotation key\n148: \n149: ### Phase 2: Reconciler Implementation\n150: - [ ] Implement Reconciler struct with Client and Scheme\n151: - [ ] Implement Reconcile method with annotation parsing\n152: - [ ] Handle time parsing and expiration logic\n153: - [ ] Implement delete with NotFound handling\n154: \n155: ### Phase 3: Binary Setup\n156: - [ ] Create cmd/agentd/main.go\n157: - [ ] Register Sandbox scheme\n158: - [ ] Configure controller-runtime manager\n159: - [ ] Register controller with manager\n160: \n161: ### Phase 4: Testing\n162: - [ ] Unit test for expiration detection\n163: - [ ] Unit test for annotation parsing errors\n164: - [ ] Unit test for NotFound handling\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## Acceptance Criteria\n169: \n170: - [ ] Controller watches Sandbox resources from `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n171: - [ ] Reads `last-activity-time` annotation from workloadmanager package\n172: - [ ] Deletes Sandbox after 15 minutes of inactivity\n173: - [ ] Returns RequeueAfter for non-expired sandboxes\n174: - [ ] Handles missing annotation (no-op)\n175: - [ ] Handles parse errors with 30-second requeue\n176: - [ ] Handles NotFound on delete as success\n177: - [ ] Binary starts with controller-runtime manager\n178: - [ ] Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n\n(End of file - total 178 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement a Kubernetes controller in `pkg/agentd` that automatically cleans up idle `Sandbox` resources by detecting the `last-activity-time` annotation and deleting sandboxes that have been inactive beyond a 15-minute threshold.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe agentcube platform creates `Sandbox` resources via the workload-manager to manage execution environments. These sandboxes consume cluster resources even when they're no longer actively processing requests. Currently, there is no mechanism to automatically clean up these idle resources, leading to resource accumulation over time.\n\n### Goal\n\nCreate a dedicated controller (`agentd`) that:\n- Watches `Sandbox` resources with the `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1` API group\n- Reads the `last-activity-time` annotation set by workload-manager\n- Deletes sandboxes that have been idle beyond the configured threshold\n\n### Value","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775858762619,"end":1775858762634}}}}
